From: urszula@violet.berkeley.edu ( Urszula Frydman )
Subject: ls -F behaves differently than ls -Fl
Index: bin/ls.c 4.3BSD

Description:
	ls -F should show "@" for all sym links, not just when the
	sym link point to a regular file.  When the sym link point to
	a directory ls -F shows "/", but ls -lF shows "@".
Repeat-By:
	do "ls -F" and "ls -lF" on /usr (for example).

